{
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposal would provide a self-contained residential unit within the curtilage of existing houses, and would be in conflict with other Local Plan policies. The proposal would be unacceptable in principle and would fail to comply with Local Plan policy SC1 (Housing Growth).",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposal would fail to provide an acceptable standard of accommodation for the occupiers of the new dwelling and 25 Heather Close by reason of inadequate external amenity space. It is therefore contrary to Local Plan Policy SC5 (Ensuring suitable internal and external space) and London Plan Policy D6 (Housing quality and standards).",
    "Reason : 3 - The applicant has failed to demonstrate that the proposal would not result in harm to highway and pedestrian safety, contrary to Local Plan policy EC2 (Developing a Sustainable Local Transport Network) and the Residential Crossovers and Off-Street Parking Policy.",
    "Reason : 4 - The submitted energy statement fails to demonstrate that the development would maximise energy savings at each step of the energy hierarchy. It is therefore contrary to Local Plan Policies EQ1 (Energy and Carbon Reduction) and EQ2 (Sustainable design and construction) and London Plan Policies SI2 (Minimising Greenhouse Gas Emissions)."
  ],
